Please execute the below steps before running test(s) in Makefile flow :

1. Source env.sh and setup.sh to get arc shell with required licences based on configuration.
   (This step1 is also covered in <RP_ROOTDIR>/env/README to get resousrces and setup)
  a. For SM_4x4
  -> source $RP_ROOTDIR/env/sm_4x4/env.sh   
  -> source $RP_ROOTDIR/env/sm_4x4/setup.sh   
  b. For SM_3x4 (TBD)
  -> source $RP_ROOTDIR/env/sm_3x4/env.sh   
  -> source $RP_ROOTDIR/env/sm_3x4/setup.sh   

//===============================
// Command to run a single test
//===============================

1. Below command needs to be run only once based on configuration : 
   a. For sm_4x4
      Go to $RP_ROOTDIR/verification/scripts/sm_4x4 
   -> gmake -f Makefile.mk cmplib 

   b. For sm_3x4 (TBD)
      Go to $RP_ROOTDIR/verification/scripts/sm_3x4 
   -> gmake -f Makefile.mk cmplib 

2. Below are the Makefile targets 
    Build:   ‚compiles the design and the testbench 
    Run  :    executes the simulation 

3. Below are the Makefile options 
    TESTNAME:    This is a mandatory option to provide the test to be run out of a list of testcases 
    DUMP:     ‚  This option enables the waveform dumping
    SEED:        This is required to recreate failing scenario seeds 
    COV:      ‚  Enables functional coverage. N/A for now


4. Build and run simulation command
  a. For sm_4x4 
     Go to $RP_ROOTDIR/verification/scripts/sm_4x4 
     gmake -f Makefile.mk build DUMP=1 && gmake -f Makefile.mk run TESTNAME=sysrp_sanity_test DUMP=1
     or
     gmake -f Makefile.mk build DUMP=1 && arc submit -PE flow/sw/bigmem mem=20000 -- "gmake -f Makefile.mk run TESTNAME=sysrp_sanity_test DUMP=1"

  b. For  sm_3x4
     Go to $RP_ROOTDIR/verification/scripts/sm_3x4
     gmake -f Makefile.mk build DUMP=1 && gmake -f Makefile.mk run TESTNAME=sysrp_sanity_test DUMP=1
     or
     gmake -f Makefile.mk build DUMP=1 && arc submit -PE flow/sw/bigmem mem=20000 -- "gmake -f Makefile.mk run TESTNAME=sysrp_sanity_test DUMP=1"

=> The simulation runs/results are under <RP_ROOTDIR>/verification/run_dir

//===============================
// Command to run a regression
// TBD
//===============================

1. Go to $RP_ROOTDIR/verification/scripts/sm_4x4 

2. Below are the options available for regression script
   cov/nocov      Enables functional and code coverage/Disables coverage

3. Regression command 
  a. For sm_4x4 or sm_3x4 configuration without coverage
     perl regress_run.pl nocov sm_4x4  (Work in progress)

  b. For sm_4x4 or sm_3x4 configuration with coverage
     perl regress_run.pl cov  sm_4x4    (Work in progress)
